President Biden recently held a virtual meeting with Prime Minister Modi of India ahead of the U.S.-India 2+2 ministerial. The two leaders had a productive conversation covering various bilateral and global issues. They discussed joint efforts to end the COVID-19 pandemic, climate change, strengthening the global economy, and upholding a free and open Indo-Pacific. The leaders also discussed Russia's war against Ukraine, with the U.S. and India partnering to mitigate its destabilizing impacts. The 2+2 ministerial will cover a wide range of topics, including energy, science and technology partnership initiatives, counterterrorism, and multilateral cooperation. The leaders' meeting served as an important touchpoint for sharing perspectives on these issues.